### 2. 📦 Request Body Parsing & Input Validation
The app has no body parser or input validation. For any route that accepts user input, add:
```js
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' })); // Prevent large payload DoS
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true, limit: '10kb' }));
```
Validate/sanitize inputs using a library like `zod`, `joi`, or `express-validator` before using them in logic.

---

### 3. 🚫 Centralized Error Handling
There's no error handler, so unhandled errors will leak stack traces or crash the process. Add a global error middleware at the end:
```js
// Catch-all for unhandled errors
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack); // Log internally only
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({
    error: 'Internal Server Error'
