app.use(limiter);
```

### 4. 🟡 Sensitive Data Exposure
The `/users` endpoint exposes email addresses without authentication. At minimum:
- Require an auth middleware before sensitive routes.
- Consider whether all fields (e.g., email) need to be returned by default.

### 5. 🟡 No Global Error Handler
Unhandled errors will leak stack traces to clients. Add a centralized error handler:

```js
// 404 handler
