  console.error(err.stack); // log internally
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});
```

### 6. 🟡 No Request Logging
Add structured request logging (e.g., [morgan](https://github.com/expressjs/morgan)) so you can audit traffic and detect abuse:

```js
const morgan = require('morgan');
app.use(morgan('combined'));
```

### 7. 🟢 Hardcoded Port
The port `3000` is hardcoded. Prefer an environment variable with a fallback:

```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```

### 8. 🟢 Health Endpoint Hardening
The `/health` endpoint is fine, but consider not exposing `timestamp` in production as it can reveal server timing information.

---

